{
  "texts": [
    "The integration of large language models (LLMs) in practical applications such as healthcare (Raza et al., 2024; Mesk and Topol, 2023; He et al., 2023), finance (Li et al., 2023; Zhao et al., 2024), legal services (Lai et al., 2023; Yang et al., 2024) has become an irresistible trend.",
    "Meanwhile, this widespread adoption has also raised concerns about the potential risk of LLMs in generating harmful content inadvertently.",
    "This has made it imperative to address the issue of jailbreaking attacks, which systematically induce harmful contents from LLMs.",
    "In response, safety measures (Bai et al., 2022b; Zhou et al., 2023; Dai et al., 2024) have been built into LLMs.",
    "Through preference learning, these measures align the output of LLMs with human values, enabling them to conscientiously reject any malicious requests."
  ]
}